OL,3,CNational Grid fined over #3m after
OL,4,Cpylon worker suffered life-changing
OL,5,Cinjuries
OL,7,F"Although I appreciate that I have
OL,8,Fbeen lucky to survive, I have to live
OL,9,Fwith the physical and mental effects
OL,10,Fof the accident for life. I also have
OL,11,Fto live with the uncertainty of the
OL,12,Flong term damage 33 thousands volts
OL,13,Fhave done to my internal organs."
OL,15,FCardiff Crown Court heard that Mr
OL,16,FHollins, also suffered nerve damage
OL,17,Fthat affects mobility, was wearing a
OL,18,Fclimbing harness and left hanging on
OL,19,Fthe pylon for some time before being
OL,20,Frescued by his colleagues.
